The Prague Stock Exchange finished with fewer points at the end of the day.
After the rapid fall of the morning, the Prague Stock Exchange corrected its losses.
Transactions of the shares reached about half the value they have on a normal day.
The Prague Stock Exchange, at the beginning of Tuesday trade, reacted immediately to Monday's fall when it fell to about 6%.
The drop this time is due to the fall in stocks on Wall Street.
Here too, the reaction of the market to the outcome of the vote of the American Assembly of Representatives that refused to support the stabilization plan of the secretary of the financial sector is expressed.
Decline in stocks in Asia
Stocks on the Asian stock exchanges experienced a dramatic drop on Tuesday, though the index eventually softened some of the losses over the course of the day.
The Hong Kong Hang Seng stock market index over its financial day was nearly four percent, although it later softened its losses by reducing the decline by nearly 2.5 percent.
The Hang Seng China Enterprises index that tracks Chinese stock movements on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange fell 3.8 percent, in Shanghai markets were closed.
Shares on the Sydney Stock Exchange lost more than five percent but, in the end, losses dropped to 4.3 percent.
The Taiwan Stock Exchange, according to the Index secretary, fell to 3.6 percent.
“The rescue actions scheduled in the U.S. are insecure and this influences the financial market around the world,” said Hong Kong’s Chief Currency Officer Joseph Yam.
Although Hong Kong is a part of China, it only determines its monetary policy, that is, without dependence on the Central Bank of China.
Hong Kong’s interest rates are at the same level as those of the United States.
U.S. lawmakers should meet again as soon as possible, according to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, and approve a proposal to support the financial system.
Otherwise, it threatens that the falls will be felt in other countries.
Bloody Bathing of American Stocks
On Monday, the American Assembly of Representatives rejected the plan to help the financial system to which it should devote $700 billion (almost 12 trillion kronor).
Lawmakers, in that way, ignored President George Bush’s invitation to support his plan.
For Bush, the plan would solve the root causes of the financial crisis and help stabilize the entire economy.
On Monday, U.S. stocks experienced a bloody bath and mainly the stock index picked up the biggest drop in more than 20 years.
The Dow Jones index dropped to nearly seven percent, with a similar volume drop last recorded in 1987.
The index went down before it was announced but as soon as it was shown that the proposal of the assembly did not go forward, the index began to fall freely.
Congress Withdraws: U.S. Government May Inject $700 Billion into Banking
The highest representatives of Congress and the government, President George W. Bush, agreed on a broad-based pact of financial aid to the American financial system.
The vote will take place early next week.
U.S. lawmakers have caused a gap in talks about approving the bailout plan in its form of aid to the U.S. financial system with the amount of $700 billion (approximately 12 trillion kronor).
However, it is not yet won.
Congress must fine-tune some details of the contract before they can make the final form of the law public and get it voted on.
The plan to help the financial system will be discussed Monday in the Assembly of Representatives.
He told Reuters on Sunday, Barney Frank, chairman of the Assembly’s Committee on Financial Services and Banking.
According to some sources, the vote on the plan could be held in the Senate no earlier than Wednesday.
According to economists, the arrival of the rescue plan ratification should represent the announcement of a psychologically significant first factor for the revitalization of the financial market.
Then, however, “disenchantment” will be achieved thanks to the complex mechanisms whose aid to the market will also reach in practice.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
“We have made a great breakthrough.
We have resolved our disagreeing views on how the package of measures for stabilizing the market should be done,” Democrat Nancy Pelosiá told Bloomberg.
According to her, the final vote could still be held on Sunday.
Representatives of lawmakers met Sunday night with Finance Minister Henry Paulson to give a definitive shape to the government fund.
It should buy from financial corporations the unsold mortgage assets that take financial firms to hard losses and threaten the stability of the entire system.
“We are about to close the agreement on the plan, which will work and should also be effective in the market.
We still need to continue with the sanitation plan, but I think we’re already in it,” Paulson said.
A Sign for Asian Business
The global financial crisis has an explicit impact on the rapidly falling stock market.
According to Nevada Democratic Senator Harry Reid, lawmakers are doing everything they can to get Congress to definitively pass a deal this Sunday.
They want to reassure investors of the Asian financial market as these are the ones in the first time zone and where Congress could influence Monday’s trade.
However, for now there is nothing clear about when the two chambers of Congress will vote and, not even, if they will not stall at the last moment with some problem.
Lawmakers expect it to be passed in the coming days.
The law, however, will undergo a number of changes.
The total amount intended to help the system must be divided into two parts.
The first $350 billion needs to be made available as soon as possible, as President George Bush has requested.
However, Congress can block the release of the remaining amount if it has the impression that the program does not fulfill its function, which would be another $100 billion and, later, the last $350 billion.
Bush praised the progress of the meetings.
On the other hand, the president can veto this decision but Congress can overcome his veto by a majority of votes.
Despite these changes, the basic idea of the program of earning financial resources for the repurchase of bad mortgage bonds was preserved, the value of which fell because hundreds of thousands of Americans are unable to finish paying off their mortgages.
“We have worked everything.
The Assembly of Representatives would have to be prepared to vote on the bill on Sunday, and the Senate on Monday,” said Republican Senator Judd Gregg.
U.S. President Bush is also pleased with the progress of the meetings.
His spokesman, Tony Fratto, announced that Bush is pleased with Saturday’s move and that he values “the commitment of both sides to stabilizing our financial market and protecting our economy.”
Limitation of the armored contract
Senate Banking Committee Chairman Christopher Dodd, chief negotiator, said lawmakers decided on the responsibility of program money for protecting taxpayers’ taxes from their losses, a soothing closure of the planned finance plan.
The new law should also limit so-called armoured contracts for directors of participating companies, and create a committee that will have control of the Fund.
This would have to be directed by the Ministry of Finance.
“We’ve worked very hard on it, and we’ve made a major breakthrough toward the agreement that will work and be effective for the market and for all Americans,” Paulson said.
The plan also includes helping homeowners who have problems with their payments.
The government would have to agree to the new mortgage payments it buys in order to lower the monthly charges on debtors’ installments and enable them to keep their homes.
Marek: psychological help
The proposed plan is, according to Patria Finance chief economist David Marek, a good idea that will be realized but quite difficult.
“And that’s why it’s not known by what mechanism and at what price the problematic assets will be bought.
This will be decisive for the sharing of losses between the financial sector and the government,” Marek said this week, for the iHNed.cz server.
Whether the plan is approved now or early next week is not, according to Marek, as relevant.
“Much more important is that already this week the congressmen agree on their support and give them their approval as soon as possible.
This important and psychological agreement that this approval is reached is, at the moment, the most important thing,” Marek insisted.
