It is said that a rat or a cockroach feeling danger flees, why is it also afraid?
Joseph Le Doux, a scientist in the field of neurology, is convinced that many animals also have feelings.
How can you control whether they, behaving in a similar way to us, feel the same way?
An internet magazine called "Edge" has been publishing contributions from famous scientists for many years.
