Very soon, on October 8, the criminal trial against János Zuschlag and his accomplices will begin.
The politician and his accomplices are accused of committing frauds of significant damage, in a business manner, continuously and in an organized form in addition to other crimes, including the falsification of documents.
According to the Prosecutor’s Office, they used the funds obtained in public tenders for their own purposes, often justifying the fulfillment of tasks with false invoices.
The public funds and that of the municipalities - in total about 65 million HUF - ended partly in the treasury of the organization Fiatal Baloldal and partly in the pocket of individuals.
The method, which was made known by the researchers as well, was to justify the collection of funds obtained in public tenders with false invoices behind which there was no actual execution, the different associations never fulfilled their obligations assumed.
